A man wielding a knife was able to jump the White House fence just over a week ago.

Now, the Secret Service has been accused of fumbling its response to another threat.

Officers allegedly performed a string of security lapses after gunman Oscar Ramiro Ortega-Hernandez fired around eight bullets at the executive mansion in November 2011.

