Although President Obama, his wife Michelle and their older daughter Malia were not at home at the time, their younger daughter Sasha and Mrs Obama's mother, Marian Robinson, were inside. 

In accordance with protocol, Secret Service officers rushed to respond, with one stationed under the second-floor terrace withdrawing her handgun and snipers on the roof preparing for action.

However, they reportedly halted their response when they were wrongly informed, 'No shots have been fired... stand down', by their supervisor.

The supervisor claimed the noise had instead stemmed from the backfire from a nearby construction vehicle, according to information obtained by the Washington Post. 

